meta {
  name: 1.3 Steven Put influencer - NO RAG
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/ask/no-rag
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "question": "Is Steven Put an influencer? He seems to travel a lot."
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: true
}

docs {
  # Beat 1 — the problem (the fun one)

  Plain LLM, **no retrieval**. The model doesn't know who Steven Put is, but the
  leading phrasing ("seems to travel a lot") will tempt it to play along and
  invent a plausible-sounding influencer backstory.

  **Expected:** a confident, fabricated character sketch — exactly the kind of
  fluent nonsense RAG exists to stop.

  Pair with `2.3 Steven Put influencer - naive RAG`, which can only say what the
  newsletters actually mention about Steven (e.g. real travel / project notes).
}
